Present Perfect 4
1.
1) She has been in Ireland since Monday.
2) I've known her for a long time.
3) Sarah and Andy are married. They have been married since 2005.
4) Ben is ill. He has been ill for the last few days.
5) We live in Scott Road. We have lived there for a long time.
6) Kate works in a bank. She has worked there for five years.
7) Alan has a headache. He has had a headache since he got up this morning.
8) I'm learning English. I have been learning English for six months.
2.
1) How long has she been on holiday?
2) How long have they been in Brazil?
3) How long have you known Amy?
4) How long has Emily been learning Italian?
5) How long has your brother lived in Canada?
6) How long have you been a teacher?
7) How long has it been raining?
3.
1) They have been married for ten years.
2) She has lived in Wales all her life.
3) They have been on holiday since Sunday.
4) The sun has been shining all day.
5) She has been waiting for ten minutes.
6) He has had a beard since he was 20.
4.
1) Mark has lived in Canada since April.
2) Jane and I are friends. I know her very well.
3) Jane and I are friends. I've known her for a long time.
4) Sorry I'm late. How long have you been waiting? Not long. Only 5 minutes.
5) Luke works in a hotel now. He likes his job a lot.
6) Ruth is reading a newspaper. She has been reading it for two hours.
7) How long have you lived in this house? About ten years.
8) Is that a new coat? No, I've had this coat for a long time.
9) Tom is in Spain at the moment. He has been there for the last three days.
5.
1) We have lived in this house since 2008.
2) How long have you been friends with Lara?
3) The children have been watching TV since 6 o'clock.
4) Sally has known Ben for a long time.
5) It has been snowing all morning.
6) Has Sasha been learning Spanish for a long time?
7) I'm ill. I've spent all day in bed.
8) How long have Kevin and Alla been married?
